Elephants, Alcohol and Benefits Divide Botswana Ruling Party
Botswana’s New Leader Backs Asset Sales in Investment Drive
Khama is the son of the country’s first president, Seretse Khama, and still yields some influence in the nation of 2.3 million people. The BDP will compete, among others, against the Khama-linked breakaway party that’s formed a loose alliance with the Umbrella for Democratic Change coalition. To contact the reporter on this story:
